headline: BlackRock’s Assets Expected to Hit New Record
summary: Wall Street expects BlackRock to post higher profits and assets under management when the firm releases earnings Tuesday, following a volatile second quarter for investors.  Analysts are calling for BlackRock to report per-share earnings of $10.06, or $10.78 on an adjusted basis, on revenue of $5.45 billion.  The world’s largest money manager, best known for its vast fund offerings and influential chief executive, Larry Fink, is expected to report a record $12.15 trillion of client assets.

headline: Japan Is Worrying the Bond Market. How Treasuries Can Avoid a Slump, for Now.
summary: President Donald Trump repeated his demand for the Federal Reserve to cut interest rates on Monday, claiming the U.S. should have the lowest in the world and save billions in government borrowing costs.  Tom Parker and Jeffery Rosenberg, who run  BlackRock’s  Systematic Fixed Income team, describe a “new conundrum” for bond markets tied to inflation uncertainty, rising debt sales, and falling global demand.  “Longer-term interest rates can rise even as the Fed is expected to cut rates,” the pair wrote in a recent market outlook report.
